---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SNU JPL Research - Mosquito-Borne Disease Prediction"
  pageClass="hero-page"
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-overlay">
        <div class="container">
          <h2>Predicting Mosquito-Borne Disease Outbreaks</h2>
          <p>
            Southern Nazarene University collaborates with NASA JPL to develop a
            risk model for mosquito-borne diseases using remote sensing data in
            Oklahoma.
          </p>
          <div class="button-group">
            <a href="/project" class="demo-button">Project Details</a>
            <a href="/methods" class="demo-button">Methods</a>
            <a href="/team" class="demo-button">Meet the Team</a>
          </div>
          <a href="/project" class="cta-button">Explore the Project</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="content">
      <div class="container">
        <h3>Project Overview</h3>
        <p>
          Our team of six SNU undergraduate students, mentored by Dr. Caio
          Fran√ßa and Dr. Erika Podest (NASA JPL), is working to predict
          mosquito-borne disease outbreaks. By analyzing in situ and spaceborne
          remote sensing data, we aim to identify environmental and land cover
          predictors of mosquito abundance in Oklahoma, with potential
          applications to other regions like Costa Rica.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Three focus groups explore correlations, land cover classification,
            and remote sensing data.
          </li>
          <li>
            Using tools like Google Earth Engine, R, and Google Colab for data
            analysis.
          </li>
          <li>
            Collaborating with NASA JPL through the Maximizing Student Potential
            program.
          </li>
          <li>
            Addressing key research questions on mosquito ecology and disease
            risk.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
